                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>1999-06-18</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This is a very nice little book, and I found it to be surprisingly readable. The book is nicely written. Standard ML is used to illustrate the technique of compiling a functional language using continuations as the primary intermediate representation. Lack of familiarity with ML is not particularly burdensome. I would like to have seen more discussion of other languages, though (Scheme?).</span>
                  
              
